**Category:** essay-draft fideism skepticism epistemology postmodernism

**Abstract:**
A shorter variant of the April 23, 1996 essay on "Fideism and Skepticism." Argues that if the Enlightenment's standard of rationality is valid, skepticism follows; but the standard arises from a Greek misconception of knowledge. Distinguishes between knowing as theoretical view requiring assent and knowing as "applicative tool," noting that nobody is a practical skeptic because knowing and acting are intrinsically connected.

**AI Recommendation:** Variant draft of 96-APR-3 essay; compare versions.

